                                                                <div data-widget-id="wid__text__5f4e4cee46468" class="moto-widget moto-widget-text moto-preset-default  moto-spacing-top-small moto-spacing-right-auto moto-spacing-bottom-large moto-spacing-left-auto  " data-widget="text" data-preset="default" data-spacing="sala" data-visible-on="mobile-v" data-animation="">
                                                                    <div class="moto-widget-text-content moto-widget-text-editable">
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“Oh, the depth of the riches both of the wisdom and knowledge of God! How unsearchable are His judgments and His ways past finding out!”
                                                                            <b>Romans 11:33 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“ For My thoughts are not your thoughts, Nor are your ways My ways,” says the LORD. “For as the heavens are higher than the earth, So are My ways higher than your ways, And My thoughts than your thoughts.”
                                                                            <b>Isaiah 55:8-9 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">“He has made the earth by His power; He has established the world by His wisdom, And stretched out the heaven by His understanding. When He utters His voice— There is a multitude of waters in the heavens: “He causes the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth; He makes lightnings for the rain; He brings the wind out of His treasuries.”
                                                                            <b>Jeremiah 51:15-16 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">As we see as each day passes the attributes build one upon the other.  Delicately intertwined Wisdom continues the tapestry.  In order to have wisdom one must have knowledge.  God is all knowing so He is all wisdom.  Wisdom is not just knowledge but the “know how”, the ability to see the best, for the most for the longest time even unto eternity always for His Glory.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Let’s go back to the Garden of Eden.  When God said thou shalt not eat from the tree of the knowledge of good and evil His instruction came from pure knowledge and wisdom of the long term effects.  Adam and Eve had knowledge that the tree was there, but not of the consequences of their disobedience, therefore they choose their own wisdom/way to the conclusion they wanted to follow through with the temptation.  What seemed to thrust humanity into a tailspin, God in His foreknowledge and wisdom already had orchestrated the redemption of mankind through Christ His son, the Lamb without spot or blemish to die for the redemption of mankind, which always was the best, for the most for all eternity.  God has never backtracked nor had to come up with another plan.  His plan was laid out before the foundations of the world.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The take away for our life is simple.  We don’t want to follow <b>Isaiah 53:6</b> which states, “all have turned to their own way.”  SIN!  We turn to our own way because we think we are wiser than God.  What is our choice today, to follow the wisdom of God?  Who tells us  “If any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all liberally and without reproach, and it will be given to him.”  <b>James 1:5 NKJV</b>
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Wisdom can only be found by revelation from God, for we cannot find it by our own efforts.
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">The Lord is willing to give us all wisdom in all situations.  We only need to ask.  Let us not choose our own path, but pause, seek and trust Him, not leaning on our understanding, but acknowledge Him and He will direct us.  This is a promise!  Grasp it!
                                                                        </p>
                                                                        <p><br></p>
                                                                        <p class="moto-text_system_10">Today as we bow before you Lord we are seeking the strength, courage and wisdom to know the guidance You desire us to follow.  We have missed the mark many times, made many mistakes by not seeking and applying Your wisdom to our lives.  Let this be forever
                                                                            changed as we turn a corner and come to understanding and having the “know” from You of what needs to be done, and the how to accomplish it.  We pray in the blessed name of Jesus Christ our Lord.  Amen
                                                                        </p>
